  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-11-09",
    "date": "2021-12-01T19:13:45Z",
    "text": "Veterans Heroin Overdose Prevention Examination Act or the Veterans HOPE Act\n\nThis bill requires the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to complete a review of the deaths of all covered veterans who died from opioid overdoses during the five-year period preceding the enactment of this bill. Covered veterans are those who received VA hospital care or medical services during the five-year period preceding the death of the veteran.\n\nThe VA shall report on the results of the review and make such report publicly available."
  },
